50
00:03:39,826 --> 00:03:44,497
I've made up my mind! I'm giving up
Dog-<i>san</i>, and I will become Cat-<i>san</i>!

51
00:03:44,497 --> 00:03:49,993
<i>I truly meant what I said.</i>
<i>Tears really did come forth.</i>

52
00:03:51,171 --> 00:03:54,641
<i>I was so avid, that if there were</i>
<i>such a thing as a Cat fan club,</i>

53
00:03:54,641 --> 00:03:56,509
<i>I would absolutely join it.</i>

54
00:03:56,509 --> 00:03:58,511
<i>And yet, to be hated by him...</i>

55
00:03:58,511 --> 00:04:03,211
<i>I am a fool. A real fool. Mother...</i>

56
00:04:05,185 --> 00:04:06,853
Picking up Tohru-<i>kun</i>'s vibes...

57
00:04:06,853 --> 00:04:09,189
Ah, there she is.

58
00:04:09,189 --> 00:04:11,858
What are you kneeling for in a place
like this? Class is about to beg--

59
00:04:11,858 --> 00:04:16,529
Ee-yow! It hurts so bad, t- the tears...!

60
00:04:16,529 --> 00:04:19,532
No, really, I just bumped
the corner here, the corner...

61
00:04:19,532 --> 00:04:23,803
Somehow, it looked as
though you hit it on purpose.

62
00:04:23,803 --> 00:04:27,474
And so? You skipped out just like
that and came back home, then?

63
00:04:27,474 --> 00:04:29,476
I want to leave this house.

64
00:04:29,476 --> 00:04:31,644
It's only been three days, right?

65
00:04:31,644 --> 00:04:35,148
Think of this as training
too, and put up with it.

66
00:04:35,148 --> 00:04:38,485
I say nothing but
terrible things... to her.

67
00:04:38,485 --> 00:04:41,821
To her? You mean to Tohru-<i>kun</i>?

68
00:04:41,821 --> 00:04:45,492
Uh-huh. You yelled at her again with
the same tone as you always use, right?

69
00:04:45,492 --> 00:04:48,561
If it gets you down afterward,
you could just not yell, you know.

70
00:04:48,561 --> 00:04:50,830
Such a wretched temperament.

71
00:04:50,830 --> 00:04:55,835
It's no use. I'm just not cut out for
associating and living with people.

72
00:04:55,835 --> 00:04:58,671
There are people who are
like that, but in your case,

73
00:04:58,671 --> 00:05:03,176
it just comes from not having
enough experience with them.

74
00:05:03,176 --> 00:05:08,081
For example, with one fist,
you can break a table in half.

75
00:05:08,081 --> 00:05:11,518
However, you can also make
that fist stop just short of it.

76
00:05:11,518 --> 00:05:13,520
That's because you can control
by yourself how much power

77
00:05:13,520 --> 00:05:15,855
to portion out your fist, right?

78
00:05:15,855 --> 00:05:18,491
That's also why you were successful
when fighting with bears and stuff

79
00:05:18,491 --> 00:05:19,859
--while training in the mountains.
--I didn't fight them!

80
00:05:19,859 --> 00:05:25,491
Look, you. It's the same with
getting along well with other people.

81
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:29,869
It's just that this training
can't be done in the mountains.

82
00:05:29,869 --> 00:05:33,473
It has to be done in the
cities, where people live.

83
00:05:33,473 --> 00:05:35,041
Unless you interact with people,

84
00:05:35,041 --> 00:05:38,645
hurting them and being hurt by
them as you learn about them,

85
00:05:38,645 --> 00:05:41,481
as well as learn about yourself,

86
00:05:41,481 --> 00:05:45,577
you'll never become the kind of person
who can be concerned about others.

87
00:05:46,820 --> 00:05:49,823
Even though you may have a
black belt in the martial arts,

88
00:05:49,823 --> 00:05:51,491
you still have a white belt
at getting along with others.

89
00:05:51,491 --> 00:05:54,260
In order for you to become
able to cherish a girl,

90
00:05:54,260 --> 00:05:56,162
who at some point is kind enough
to tell you that she likes you,

91
00:05:56,162 --> 00:05:58,832
right now, you have to continue
to train, without running away.

92
00:05:58,832 --> 00:06:01,501
There'll never be anyone like that.

93
00:06:01,501 --> 00:06:02,836
But if there were, what would you do?

94
00:06:02,836 --> 00:06:07,507
I can't even imagine.
First, I'd ask if she was crazy.

95
00:06:07,507 --> 00:06:08,508
I see.

96
00:06:08,508 --> 00:06:09,843
I'm home!

97
00:06:09,843 --> 00:06:11,511
Ah, welcome back.

98
00:06:11,511 --> 00:06:12,512
Where's Tohru-<i>kun</i>?

99
00:06:12,512 --> 00:06:16,216
Working. She said she'll
be coming back around 11:00,

100
00:06:16,216 --> 00:06:17,517
so I was thinking of
going to pick her up.

101
00:06:17,517 --> 00:06:19,686
Yeah, do that for her.

102
00:06:19,686 --> 00:06:22,246
There have really been a lot
of molesters around lately.

103
00:06:24,791 --> 00:06:30,129
<i>I worked a full day today too.</i>
<i>I wonder if everyone is asleep already.</i>

104
00:06:30,129 --> 00:06:34,701
<i>I'll bet Kyo-san hasn't</i>
<i>eaten supper again tonight.</i>

105
00:06:34,701 --> 00:06:38,805
<i>He's still angry... or what</i>
<i>if he left the house entirely!?</i>

106
00:06:38,805 --> 00:06:41,001
<i>You're nasty to look at!</i>

107
00:06:42,141 --> 00:06:44,477
<i>What will I do?</i>

108
00:06:44,477 --> 00:06:47,480
<i>Tohru, you just be yourself.</i>

109
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:49,482
Yes, Mother!

110
00:06:49,482 --> 00:06:51,678
<i>I will not be discouraged.</i>

111
00:06:54,821 --> 00:06:57,655
<i>W- what was that sound?</i>

112
00:07:00,493 --> 00:07:05,832
Maybe it's... a molester...
like I've heard about...!

113
00:07:05,832 --> 00:07:07,130
No!!

114
00:07:15,508 --> 00:07:19,913
<i>I couldn't say that I mistook him</i>
<i>for a molester! That would be rude!</i>

115
00:07:19,913 --> 00:07:23,008
<i>But I just yelled "No!"</i>
<i>as loud as I could...</i>

116
00:07:24,784 --> 00:07:27,220
U- um, just a moment!
That was a practice swing.

117
00:07:27,220 --> 00:07:28,121
I just happened to get lucky today.

118
00:07:28,121 --> 00:07:30,790
Kyo-<i>san</i>, are you out for a walk?
Let's see... do you like the school?

119
00:07:30,790 --> 00:07:34,386
Stop saying "<i>san</i>" after my name!
It irritates me. You can do without it.

120
00:07:35,461 --> 00:07:39,465
--Kyo-<i>kun...</i>
--What do you want?

121
00:07:39,465 --> 00:07:41,134
I was just trying it out.

122
00:07:41,134 --> 00:07:44,137
--Don't call on me
without a reason!
--Right!

123
00:07:44,137 --> 00:07:49,475
No, I mean... that's okay...
calling on me without a reason...

124
00:07:49,475 --> 00:07:52,412
It's okay for you to
hang around in front of me,

125
00:07:52,412 --> 00:07:56,816
and if I do anything that upsets you,
you can hit me like you just did.

126
00:07:56,816 --> 00:07:59,118
<i>Could this possibly mean...</i>

127
00:07:59,118 --> 00:08:02,488
<i>he's trying to apologize</i>
<i>about what happened today?</i>

128
00:08:02,488 --> 00:08:05,825
<i>Is that the reason why he is here?</i>

129
00:08:05,825 --> 00:08:08,161
<i>Come to think of it,</i>
<i>there was that other time...</i>

130
00:08:08,161 --> 00:08:09,595
<i>That other time,</i>

131
00:08:09,595 --> 00:08:12,498
<i>when he might have been trying</i>
<i>to apologize for hurting me...</i>

132
00:08:12,498 --> 00:08:14,500
A- ahem...

133
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:16,769
I'm sorry, that wasn't it!

134
00:08:16,769 --> 00:08:19,505
The reason I hit you with my bag is
because I mistook you for a molester!

135
00:08:19,505 --> 00:08:20,506
Molester?

136
00:08:20,506 --> 00:08:23,443
So you see, it's not
that I was upset at you!

137
00:08:23,443 --> 00:08:25,111
Quite the contrary, I...

138
00:08:25,111 --> 00:08:27,113
...like you!

139
00:08:27,113 --> 00:08:30,783
I like the Cat from the zodiac!

140
00:08:30,783 --> 00:08:35,455
That is to say, um,
I... want to be friends!

141
00:08:35,455 --> 00:08:40,484
<i>If there were one, what would you do?</i>
<i>A girl who says she likes you?</i>

142
00:08:41,794 --> 00:08:45,465
There isn't anything good about the Cat!

143
00:08:45,465 --> 00:08:47,263
Let's hurry up and go home.

144
00:08:51,471 --> 00:08:56,142
<i>I've started to somewhat</i>
<i>understand Kyo-kun.</i>

145
00:08:56,142 --> 00:08:58,711
<i>He's a little more awkward than others,</i>

146
00:08:58,711 --> 00:09:02,148
<i>but he's certainly a</i>
<i>good person deep down.</i>

147
00:09:02,148 --> 00:09:06,381
<i>He's a gentle person, who</i>
<i>knows when he feels sorry.</i>

148
00:09:09,822 --> 00:09:10,923
Yesterday, you know,

149
00:09:10,923 --> 00:09:14,494
Kyo-<i>kun</i> said he was going to go
pick up Tohru-<i>kun</i> on his own!

150
00:09:14,494 --> 00:09:17,163
Kyo-<i>kun</i>, you pervert!

151
00:09:17,163 --> 00:09:19,165
How do you figure that!?

152
00:09:19,165 --> 00:09:22,769
Yesterday was special. I won't do
it again! It'll never happen again!

153
00:09:22,769 --> 00:09:27,340
Right. I'm just happy
that you're having your meal.

154
00:09:27,340 --> 00:09:30,139
How is it? Is it to your liking?

155
00:09:33,780 --> 00:09:35,448
--What!?
--Nothing.

156
00:09:35,448 --> 00:09:36,783
You were looking at me, weren't you!?

157
00:09:36,783 --> 00:09:38,117
Only looking, right?

158
00:09:38,117 --> 00:09:40,453
Why would you look at me for no reason?

159
00:09:40,453 --> 00:09:41,454
