Let's play Rich Man, Poor Man!

162
00:09:58,137 --> 00:10:01,808
Why don't you tell Yuki to? Damn Yuki!

163
00:10:01,808 --> 00:10:04,811
If you're running away from
a fight, then you're no man!

164
00:10:04,811 --> 00:10:06,145
How pathetic!

165
00:10:06,145 --> 00:10:08,481
I accept your challenge to this fight!

166
00:10:08,481 --> 00:10:10,483
You're going to be sorry
you did that, Yankee!

167
00:10:10,483 --> 00:10:15,183
Why should I? Whoever loses has to take
on the cleaning chores for everyone here!

168
00:10:16,823 --> 00:10:19,158
What a pleasant maelstrom of vibes...!

169
00:10:19,158 --> 00:10:24,392
Let's invite Sohma-<i>kun</i> this time around,
too! Where do you suppose he's gone?

170
00:10:26,432 --> 00:10:33,106
Sorry. Right now, I don't feel like
seeing anybody, so I have to say--

171
00:10:33,106 --> 00:10:37,100
No! I don't want to hear it! Yuki-<i>kun</i>!

172
00:10:42,448 --> 00:10:45,451
I, uh...

173
00:10:45,451 --> 00:10:49,582
Yuki-<i>kun</i>, you are nice...

174
00:10:51,791 --> 00:10:55,461
...but there's something
about you that rejects others.

175
00:10:55,461 --> 00:10:59,232
Everyone says so!
"Yuki-<i>kun</i> is 'special'," they say.

176
00:10:59,232 --> 00:11:03,294
"An 'ordinary' girl isn't good
enough to match up with Yuki-<i>kun."</i>

177
00:11:07,140 --> 00:11:08,141
"Revolution!"

178
00:11:08,141 --> 00:11:11,477
Why, you! What kind of dirty tricks
are you pulling, you rotten boy!?

179
00:11:11,477 --> 00:11:13,146
That's how the rules go!

180
00:11:13,146 --> 00:11:16,149
Let's see, a Revolution makes
the strong cards weak, so...

181
00:11:16,149 --> 00:11:20,814
Special move--Reverse Revolution!

182
00:11:21,821 --> 00:11:24,490
--You've had it now, Sohma!
--Nice going, Hanajima-<i>san</i>!

183
00:11:24,490 --> 00:11:26,159
Whoa, how embarrassing!

184
00:11:26,159 --> 00:11:29,527
Shut up, you guys!
This game's just getting started!

185
00:11:32,498 --> 00:11:36,196
<i>Yuki-kun, there's something</i>
<i>about you that rejects others.</i>

186
00:11:46,179 --> 00:11:48,514
Rich Man, Poor Man, huh?

187
00:11:48,514 --> 00:11:51,851
I know the rules, but I've never played.

188
00:11:51,851 --> 00:11:56,522
I just learned how to play
from Uo-<i>chan</i> myself.

189
00:11:56,522 --> 00:11:58,524
Next time, let's play it together!

190
00:11:58,524 --> 00:12:02,862
So, he was the Poor Man today, then?

191
00:12:02,862 --> 00:12:04,864
Um, we'll help you, too!

192
00:12:04,864 --> 00:12:06,532
No! My loss is my loss.

193
00:12:06,532 --> 00:12:07,867
But...

194
00:12:07,867 --> 00:12:09,869
Next time, though, I'm
going to win for sure!

195
00:12:09,869 --> 00:12:11,537
And of course, I will beat you too!

196
00:12:11,537 --> 00:12:14,540
Don't you get tired of
always saying that?

197
00:12:14,540 --> 00:12:17,543
It is my conviction to win
against you! My objective!

198
00:12:17,543 --> 00:12:21,214
And having you always badgering me
with it is my annoyance! My misfortune!

199
00:12:21,214 --> 00:12:24,483
Your attitude of looking down
upon others makes me sick!

200
00:12:24,483 --> 00:12:28,487
Your overly simplistic way
of thinking makes me sick.

201
00:12:28,487 --> 00:12:29,989
<i>They're fighting again.</i>

202
00:12:29,989 --> 00:12:36,162
<i>They get along worse than just being</i>
<i>Rat-san and Cat-san accounts for.</i>

203
00:12:36,162 --> 00:12:38,497
<i>Come to think of it, there</i>
<i>was that time earlier...</i>

204
00:12:38,497 --> 00:12:42,835
I will win against you, and
become a member of the Sohmas!

205
00:12:42,835 --> 00:12:47,006
<i>Could those words indeed mean</i>
<i>that if Kyo-kun beats Sohma-kun,</i>

206
00:12:47,006 --> 00:12:51,844
<i>he will be allowed to join the zodiac?</i>

207
00:12:51,844 --> 00:12:53,512
<i>In other words...</i>

208
00:12:53,512 --> 00:12:57,516
<i>In other words, Cat-san will be included,</i>
<i>and the Twelve will become Thirteen!</i>

209
00:12:57,516 --> 00:12:59,518
<i>That would be wonderful!</i>

210
00:12:59,518 --> 00:13:02,188
Damn you! I'll pulverize you!

211
00:13:02,188 --> 00:13:05,524
However, fighting will not do. Not at all.

212
00:13:05,524 --> 00:13:06,859
Um, Kyo-<i>kun--</i>

213
00:13:06,859 --> 00:13:09,727
Prepare yourself, you cold-blooded rat!

214
00:13:17,870 --> 00:13:20,237
Just looking at you gets on my nerves!

215
00:13:23,476 --> 00:13:24,637
Sohma-<i>kun...</i>

216
00:13:27,813 --> 00:13:29,873
Damn it all...

217
00:13:30,483 --> 00:13:34,113
Why can't I beat him?

218
00:13:35,154 --> 00:13:40,286
Today's move was a particularly
rough one. He must be in a bad mood.

219
00:13:46,499 --> 00:13:52,471
<i>As much as Sohma-kun is</i>
<i>considerate towards others,</i>

220
00:13:52,471 --> 00:13:57,705
<i>he may be the kind of person who keeps</i>
<i>his own feelings shut up inside him.</i>

221
00:14:03,516 --> 00:14:07,920
Say, guess what? There's this
incredibly good-looking kid outside.

222
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:10,189
I wonder, is it a boy or a girl?

223
00:14:10,189 --> 00:14:13,859
Oh my, how very lowbrow!

224
00:14:13,859 --> 00:14:15,088
Could that be...?

225
00:14:18,197 --> 00:14:19,597
Sohma-<i>kun</i>!

226
00:14:20,866 --> 00:14:22,468
Hey there! What a hard worker you are!

227
00:14:22,468 --> 00:14:26,138
D- did you come all the
way just to pick me up?

228
00:14:26,138 --> 00:14:30,476
Mm-hm. This is a dangerous
time for girls, and all.

229
00:14:30,476 --> 00:14:36,143
Thank you very much! Sohma-<i>kun,</i>
you and Kyo-<i>kun</i> are both kind!

230
00:14:40,152 --> 00:14:41,950
Well, shall we go?

231
00:14:43,155 --> 00:14:45,825
S- Sohma-<i>kun</i>...!

232
00:14:45,825 --> 00:14:50,996
Um, if there's anything
gloomy weighing on your mind,

233
00:14:50,996 --> 00:14:54,500
please tell me about it, okay.

234
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:55,735
When you have a bad dream,

235
00:14:55,735 --> 00:14:57,503
they say it brings good luck
to talk to someone, and all.

236
00:14:57,503 --> 00:15:00,506
So if I'm okay with you, and you want
to stamp that gloom out, I don't m--!

237
00:15:00,506 --> 00:15:04,844
Hey, there! Don't go hangin'
'round here, get on home, youngsters!

238
00:15:04,844 --> 00:15:08,848
?I can' go back to my house at all...??

239
00:15:08,848 --> 00:15:16,856
...I don't mind, but maybe I'm just
adding to your gloom instead...

240
00:15:16,856 --> 00:15:21,021
No. It's my fault for
having this nature about me.

241
00:15:26,465 --> 00:15:29,101
When I was at my parents' house,

242
00:15:29,101 --> 00:15:32,805
it was like I was in a cage, being kept
watched on by the main house and Akito.

243
00:15:32,805 --> 00:15:37,443
I was surrounded by ordinary people,
and yearned for an ordinary life.

244
00:15:37,443 --> 00:15:42,815
That's why I left the house and
began going to a coed high school.

245
00:15:42,815 --> 00:15:46,819
However, as it turns out,
I haven't left the cage at all.

246
00:15:46,819 --> 00:15:49,688
I'm still living in a
Sohma's house, same as before,

247
00:15:49,688 --> 00:15:53,492
and I can't associate
with others very well.

248
00:15:53,492 --> 00:15:55,094
It's not that I...

249
00:15:55,094 --> 00:16:00,795
mean to reject others, but there's
something about me that's awkward.

250
00:16:03,836 --> 00:16:07,006
And since I'm like this, I can't
escape my feelings of inferiority,

251
00:16:07,006 --> 00:16:08,507
or my being frightened.

252
00:16:08,507 --> 00:16:13,078
But Kyo is different. He may not take
well to those who he's unfamiliar with,

253
00:16:13,078 --> 00:16:15,514
but I think once you get to know him,

254
00:16:15,514 --> 00:16:17,516
he's the type of person
that draws others in.

255
00:16:17,516 --> 00:16:20,719
Even if he can't
become one of the zodiac,

256
00:16:20,719 --> 00:16:25,791
I think it's better for one to be able to
naturally get along with ordinary people.

257
00:16:25,791 --> 00:16:30,796
I wanted to be like that too.

258
00:16:30,796 --> 00:16:33,732
That's why it gets on my nerves.

259
00:16:33,732 --> 00:16:37,470
When I see for myself how
Kyo wants to join the Sohmas...

260
00:16:37,470 --> 00:16:41,474
I wonder what it is about me
that wants to leave there.

261
00:16:41,474 --> 00:16:45,811
Sohma-<i>kun</i>, you too have the
power to draw people in.

262
00:16:45,811 --> 00:16:50,483
So many girls say they like
you, and that you're nice.

263
00:16:50,483 --> 00:16:53,486
I'm only nice because I
want to be liked by them.

264
00:16:53,486 --> 00:16:59,492
It's like I'm giving them candy because
I want to be in their circle of friends.

265
00:16:59,492 --> 00:17:05,164
I'm only being nice for my own
sake. Maybe that's hypocritical...

266
00:17:05,164 --> 00:17:06,325
So--

267
00:17:09,835 --> 00:17:15,508
This was sure sudden. There was
nothing in the weather forecast about it.

268
00:17:15,508 --> 00:17:17,500
This is terrible!

269
00:17:18,844 --> 00:17:21,180
Sohma-<i>kun</i>...!

270
00:17:21,180 --> 00:17:25,117
What's so terrible?

271
00:17:25,117 --> 00:17:26,452
A farm?

272
00:17:26,452 --> 00:17:29,788
It's more like a family vegetable garden.

273
00:17:29,788 --> 00:17:31,790
Sohma-<i>kun</i>, you did this?

274
00:17:31,790 --> 00:17:34,460
Mm-hmm. This is my secret base.

275
00:17:34,460 --> 00:17:37,129
This is wonderful! I get it now!

276
00:17:37,129 --> 00:17:40,132
You have to protect the base from
this harsh wind and rain, right?

277
00:17:40,132 --> 00:17:43,802
I'll do whatever little
I can to help you out!

278
00:17:43,802 --> 00:17:47,139
Honda-<i>san</i>, you sure are kind!

279
00:17:47,139 --> 00:17:48,841
Ah, you can't mean it!

280
00:17:48,841 --> 00:17:52,144
This is the first time I've ever had
anyone say that to me! I'm so happy!

281
00:17:52,144 --> 00:17:54,880
Ah, but what if I too
am being hypocritical,

282
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,482
and only doing this so I will
look like a good person to others?

283
00:17:56,482 --> 00:17:58,484
No, Honda-<i>san</i>, I
think it's in your nature.

284
00:17:58,484 --> 00:18:03,489
Still, my mother always said it's
better to believe than to doubt.

285
00:18:03,489 --> 00:18:07,159
People aren't born with kindness,
you know, she would say.

286
00:18:07,159 --> 00:18:13,198
Things like our appetites, or material
desires--that's what we're all born with.

287
00:18:13,198 --> 00:18:16,502
It just means that they
are instinctive for living.

288
00:18:16,502 --> 00:18:20,139
Kindness is something that
develops, just like our bodies do,

289
00:18:20,139 --> 00:18:25,444
and the heart that grows inside
us is our conscience, she'd say.

290
00:18:25,444 --> 00:18:29,814
That's why it takes on different
forms, depending on the person.

291
00:18:32,117 --> 00:18:36,789
<i>Desire is something that everyone is</i>
<i>born with, so it's easy to comprehend.</i>

292
00:18:36,789 --> 00:18:41,794
<i>But kindness is like something which</i>
<i>people have to hand-make for themselves,</i>

293
00:18:41,794 --> 00:18:46,799
<i>so it is easily misunderstood, or</i>
<i>taken to be hypocrisy, you see.</i>

294
00:18:46,799 --> 00:18:48,767
<i>When I heard that,</i>

295
00:18:48,767 --> 00:18:52,671
<i>I was excited to think that people</i>
<i>had kindnesses that were of different</i>

296
00:18:52,671 --> 00:18:57,142
<i>shapes--like they</i>
<i>could be round, or pointy.</i>

297
00:18:57,142 --> 00:19:03,482
Sohma-<i>kun</i>, your kindness is like a
candle. Your light shines brightly.

298
00:19:03,482 --> 00:19:07,486
When it does, I become
happy, and want to smile.

299
00:19:07,486 --> 00:19:10,489
Ah, a candle must seem
pretty weird, doesn't it?

300
00:19:10,489 --> 00:19:12,891
Mm-mm! It's just--I'm really pathetic.

301
00:19:12,891 --> 00:19:15,494
Here I am a guy, yet the way I
was going on about everything...

302
00:19:15,494 --> 00:19:21,166
I'm happy you did. Sohma-<i>kun</i>, for you to
tell me so many things about yourself,

303
00:19:21,166 --> 00:19:25,228
I feel that we are getting
along that much better.

304
00:19:29,441 --> 00:19:34,113
Excuse me! I will continue
with my duty to protect the base!

305
00:19:34,113 --> 00:19:40,786
<i>Doubting is easy, it's something all</i>
<i>of us can do. Tohru, you believe.</i>

306
00:19:40,786 --> 00:19:45,124
<i>Become the kind of girl</i>
<i>who can believe in others.</i>

307
00:19:45,124 --> 00:19:51,121
<i>That will surely...</i>
<i>surely lend strength to someone.</i>

308
00:19:55,134 --> 00:19:57,136
We defended it to the last!

309
00:19:57,136 --> 00:19:59,805
But we came out of it pretty ragged.

310
00:19:59,805 --> 00:20:02,474
Is there anything that looks
ready to pick right now?

311
00:20:02,474 --> 00:20:04,810
Perhaps the leeks are ready to be eaten.

312
00:20:04,810 --> 00:20:05,811
Leeks?

313
00:20:05,811 --> 00:20:07,479
<i>Leeks... leeks...</i>

314
00:20:07,479 --> 00:20:09,148
Honda-<i>san...</i>

315
00:20:09,148 --> 00:20:13,485
Next time, I'll give
Rich Man, Poor Man a try.

316
00:20:13,485 --> 00:20:17,489
By all means! But I thought
you weren't interested in it.

317
00:20:17,489 --> 00:20:25,761
Mm-mm. It's just that it is so noisy,
I felt hesitant. But I will try.

318
00:20:27,099 --> 00:20:30,102
Little by little is okay, but I will
get better at socializing with people.

319
00:20:30,102 --> 00:20:33,872
It'll be all right! Hana-<i>chan</i>
and Uo-<i>chan</i> are very good people.

320
00:20:33,872 --> 00:20:36,108
They are the friends
that I can take pride in!

321
00:20:36,108 --> 00:20:38,410
Besides, Sohma-<i>kun</i>, you
seem like you'd be good at it,

322
00:20:38,410 --> 00:20:42,114
everyone will be delighted
over a new challenge!

323
00:20:42,114 --> 00:20:44,913
Yeah. I'm not going to give in!

324
00:20:52,124 --> 00:20:57,062
<i>I got the feeling that this was the</i>
<i>first time I saw Sohma-kun really smile.</i>

325
00:21:03,802 --> 00:21:05,471
Thank you for waiting!

326
00:21:05,471 --> 00:21:07,139
I hate leeks!

327
00:21:07,139 --> 00:21:10,142
And not just leeks either, right?
You hate onions and miso too, right?

328
00:21:10,142 --> 00:21:12,478
If the miso is in miso
soup, that's no problem!

329
00:21:12,478 --> 00:21:17,610
I did not know that. I'm sorry. I will
hurry and fix some other dish, okay?

330
00:21:19,818 --> 00:21:20,945
Eat!

331
00:21:23,155 --> 00:21:27,493
<i>Maybe there isn't anything that can be</i>
<i>done about how badly they get along.</i>

332
00:21:27,493 --> 00:21:29,528
<i>However, could it be possible</i>

333
00:21:29,528 --> 00:21:34,166
<i>that there's something about</i>
<i>Sohma-kun that appeals to Kyo?</i>

334
00:21:34,166 --> 00:21:37,503
Yuki-<i>kun</i>, Kyo-<i>kun</i> is unconscious already.

335
00:21:37,503 --> 00:21:39,772
<i>If they could understand</i>
<i>that about each other,</i>

336
00:21:39,772 --> 00:21:42,841
<i>they would get along better, maybe...</i>

337
00:21:42,841 --> 00:21:46,845
<i>I... guess I just</i>
<i>misunderstood you. I'm sorry.</i>

338
00:21:46,845 --> 00:21:51,715
<i>Me too. Let's go on, forever</i>
<i>deepening our friendship!</i>

339
00:21:52,518 --> 00:21:56,182
<i>Somehow, that's scary too!</i>

340
00:21:56,787 --> 00:22:06,786
<i>Now let us circle together,</i>
<i>around a pleasant dinner.</i>

341
00:22:06,797 --> 00:22:16,796
<i>Come, take today's tears, and</i>
<i>make them tomorrow's strength.</i>

342
00:22:17,808 --> 00:22:23,146
<i>La, la, la...</i>

343
00:22:23,146 --> 00:22:29,152
<i>Wonderful love and life</i>

344
00:22:29,152 --> 00:22:34,491
<i>La, la, la...</i>

345
00:22:34,491 --> 00:22:40,163
<i>Adorable love and life</i>

346
00:22:40,163 --> 00:22:45,502
<i>La, la, la...</i>

347
00:22:45,502 --> 00:22:49,200
<i>Wonderful love and life</i>

348
00:23:19,036 --> 00:23:22,638
On the next Fruits Basket
Episode 4...

349
00:23:22,638 --> 00:23:25,308
<i>My name is Sohma Kagura.</i>

350
00:23:25,308 --> 00:23:29,979
<i>Sohma Kagura-san? What a cute girl!</i>


351
00:23:29,979 --> 00:23:35,318
<i>In fact, Kagura has kept saying she</i>
<i>would marry Kyo since she was little.</i>


352
00:23:35,318 --> 00:23:38,321
<i>Right. Kagura-san is incredible.</i>

353
00:23:38,321 --> 00:23:40,790
<i>When she's here, things go badly for me.</i>

354
00:23:40,790 --> 00:23:42,992
<i>She never, ever</i>
<i>understands what's going on.</i>

355
00:23:42,992 --> 00:23:47,726
<i>I think it's amazing that someone</i>
<i>could come to like someone else so much.</i>


